If you access JIRA's database connection docs (more specifically the [MSSQL|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Connecting+JIRA+to+SQL+Server+2008] document), you will see that there is no mention about dynamic port assignment not being allowed.

There is a line which states that one port must be remember, but I believe we could add one line to the documentation just so it's documented that JIRA won't connect to the DB with dynamic port configured. Here is the line from the doc:

{quote}
*Remember this port number*, as it will be used to configure JIRA's connection to this database in subsequent steps.
{quote}

h3. Expected

Add one line in the documentation stating that this configuration is not supported by the JIRA application.

